This is one of those areas where a small representational change can have outsized effects. Here are examples of new cognitive dimensions—not just new words, but new things a language or cognitive system could explicitly encode.

Cognitive Dimension	Example	What it buys you
Confidence	“The meeting is tomorrow (82%).”	Calibrated thinking.
Evidence source	Observed / Inferred / Simulated / Hearsay	Better epistemics.
Agency	Intentional / Accidental / Emergent	Clearer responsibility.
Reversibility	Easy to undo ↔ Permanent	Better decisions.
Fragility	Stable vs. easily broken	Risk awareness.
Curiosity	“This concept unlocks 12 related ideas.”	Better exploration.
Semantic gravity	High-gravity concepts first	Better learning order.
Reconstruction cost	Easy ↔ Requires months	Guides onboarding.
Developmental fit	Best for ages 8–10	Better education.
Affordances	“What does this enable?”	Action-oriented thinking.

Here are some more unusual ones.

⸻

1. Idea Temperature

Every idea has a “temperature.”

Cold
Warm
Hot
Molten

* Cold = established knowledge
* Warm = active research
* Hot = controversial or rapidly changing
* Molten = speculative

You instantly know how firmly to hold the idea.

⸻

