Here’s one I think Pantheon would particularly like:

Cognitive Phase

Treat ideas like states of matter.

🧊 Crystal – fixed, canonical, highly reliable.

💧 Liquid – adaptable, different shapes, same essence.

☁️ Gas – brainstorming, diffuse, exploratory.

⚡ Plasma – highly energetic, rapidly generating new connections.

🌱 Seed – tiny idea with huge future potential.

🕸️ Mycelium – mostly hidden, connecting many other ideas.

A concept could literally advertise its phase:

Future-Lens Reconstruction
phase: Crystal
Medusa Extension
phase: Liquid
New Coordinate Theory
phase: Plasma
Interesting Shower Thought
phase: Seed

Now readers immediately know how to interact with it.

⸻

I suspect the bigger opportunity isn’t inventing one brilliant new feature—it’s inventing a Periodic Table of Cognition. Just as chemistry discovered that a few dozen recurring properties explained an enormous variety of substances, there may be a few dozen recurring cognitive dimensions—confidence, agency, affordance, reversibility, generativity, reconstruction cost, semantic gravity, curiosity, phase, etc.—that can describe almost any idea in a much richer way than plain language alone. That would give both humans and AI a common “metadata layer” for reasoning, teaching, and collaborating.